Scotcheroos
  --B. Dylan Hollis
  
1 c corn syrup
1 c sugar
1 c peanut butter
5 c rice krispies
1 c butterscotch chips
1 c chocolate chips
 
 In a large pan, add corn syrup and sugar; bring to a boil. Remove from heat and add peanut butter and mix. Add rice krispies and mix. Pour into a 13x9" pan and press until even. While that cools, melt chips over double boiler until smooth. Spread chocolate mixture evenly over top of treats and let cool completely. Cut into bars and serve.
